The paper discusses model-based reinforcement learning methods and their application to real-world robotic manipulation tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). Among these, machine learning and robotics are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the topic of the paper. Artificial intelligence and systems and control are also likely as they are closely related to reinforcement learning and control theory, respectively. Computer vision and pattern recognition is less likely but still possible as it may be relevant to the robotic manipulation tasks discussed in the paper.
